OL,7,F"When things are terrible, when you're
OL,8,Fhitting the lowest point in life, you
OL,9,Fcan at some point bounce back to try
OL,10,Fand do something and change something."
OL,12,FOn Ceri's backpack were the names of
OL,13,F450 children either fighting cancer or
OL,14,Fwho had died from cancer, many of whom
OL,15,Fhe'd met during his campaign.
OL,17,F"Those children inspire you to do
OL,18,Fthings better because they handle this
OL,19,Fthing a lot better than we do, and
OL,20,Fthey're much more brave and courageous
OL,21,Fthan we ever are."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
